<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1652,1895]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weksler, Percequillo &amp; Voss" authorityYear="2006" box="[279,439,1653,1678]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Euryoryzomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[279,439,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Euryoryzomys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises six species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Musser, Carleton, Gardner &amp; Brothers 1998)" baseAuthorityName="Musser, Carleton, Gardner &amp; Brothers" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[711,1398,1652,1678]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Euryoryzomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="emmonsae">
<emphasis box="[711,862,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. emmonsae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Musser, G. G. &amp; Carleton, M. D. &amp; Brothers, E. M. &amp; Gardner, A. L." box="[880,1389,1652,1678]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 376" refId="ref69760" refString="Musser, G. G., Carleton, M. D., Brothers, E. M. &amp; Gardner, A. L. (1998) Systematic studies of Oryzomyine rodents (Muridae, Sigmodontinae): diagnoses and distributions of species formerly assigned to Oryzomys &quot; capito &quot;. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 236, 1 - 376." type="journal article" year="1998">Musser, Carleton, Gardner &amp; Brothers 1998</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thomas 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1901" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Euryoryzomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lamia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. lamia</emphasis>
(Thomas 1901)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thomas 1925)" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[412,710,1688,1715]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Euryoryzomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="legatus">
<emphasis box="[412,526,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. legatus</emphasis>
(Thomas 1925)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thomas 1910)" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[723,1077,1688,1714]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Euryoryzomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macconnelli">
<emphasis box="[723,893,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. macconnelli</emphasis>
(Thomas 1910)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thomas 1884)" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[1090,1383,1688,1714]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Euryoryzomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis box="[1090,1198,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. nitidus</emphasis>
(Thomas 1884)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wagner 1848)" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[151,452,1724,1750]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Euryoryzomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="russatus">
<emphasis box="[151,275,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. russatus</emphasis>
(Wagner 1848)
</taxonomicName>
. The species inhabit forests throughout the cis Andean tropical and subtropical lowlands of South America, including Amazonia, the Guianas, southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[902,973,1760,1786]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1072,1157,1760,1786]" name="Bolivia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1270,1384,1760,1786]" name="Argentina" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, and eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[237,341,1797,1823]" name="Paraguay" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Musser, G. G. &amp; Carleton, M. D. &amp; Brothers, E. M. &amp; Gardner, A. L." box="[354,565,1796,1823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 376" refId="ref69760" refString="Musser, G. G., Carleton, M. D., Brothers, E. M. &amp; Gardner, A. L. (1998) Systematic studies of Oryzomyine rodents (Muridae, Sigmodontinae): diagnoses and distributions of species formerly assigned to Oryzomys &quot; capito &quot;. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 236, 1 - 376." type="journal article" year="1998">
Musser 
<emphasis box="[445,493,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 1998
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Weksler, M. &amp; Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Voss, R. S." box="[575,794,1796,1823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 29" refId="ref76039" refString="Weksler, M., Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Voss, R. S. (2006) Ten new genera of oryzomyine rodents (Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 3537, 1 - 29." type="journal article" year="2006">
Weksler 
<emphasis box="[672,721,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Percequillo, A. R." box="[803,1010,1796,1823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="312 - 320" refId="ref71297" refString="Percequillo, A. R. (2015 c) Genus Euryoryzomys Weksler, Percequillo &amp; Voss, 2006. In: Patton, J., Pardinas, U. F. J. &amp; D'Elia, G. (Eds.), Mammals of South America. 2. Rodents. University of Chicago Press, Chicago, Illinois, pp. 312 - 320." type="book chapter" year="2015">Percequillo 2015c</bibRefCitation>
). All cytogenetic data available for the genus was presented on 
<tableCitation box="[425,509,1832,1858]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="14.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,227,1756]" captionText="TABLE 3. Karyotype data of genus Euryoryzomys. Species, diploid (2n) and fundamental (FN) numbers, collection lo- calities, geographic coordinates and reference." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Table 3</tableCitation>
, and the distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens were presented on 
<figureCitation box="[362,429,1868,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1037,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-431@13.[151,1436,1029,1925]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Euryoryzomys. (■) E. emmonsae; (□) E. lamia; (▲) E. macconnelli; (○) E. nitidus; (l) E. russatus; (r) Euryoryzomys sp. nov.; (ê) Euryoryzomys sp.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423621/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
